{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-30366].
  {panel}

At the moment, the macro "Content by Label" shows all pages that fit the conditions declared in the first field of parameters. It will also show the page where it is placed on

While this will certainly make sense in some cases, it would be nice if I could specify wether or not this will happen. We have the use case that we want to show other pages with the same set of labels as "related pages", which would rule out the one the macro is placed on.

This is not a big deal, but would improve the possibilities to structure our content and guide users through it.

